Explanation:

We initialize the points and brainpower arrays to store the points and brainpower values for each question. Then, iterate through the questions array starting from the second question. For each question, check if the current brainpower is greater than or equal to the brainpower of the previous question. If it is, add the points of the current question to the maximum points and update the brainpower of the current question.

The time complexity is O(n) because we only iterate through the questions array once. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a constant amount of space for the points and brainpower arrays. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few simple operations and does not consume significant energy.

